Example 1.2 

Write a program to find the larger of two given numbers.

Algorithum: 
1. Input two numbers a and b 
2. Assign big = a
3. if (b>big) then big = b
4. Output big 
5. STOP 

#include<stdio.h>
int main(){
    float a,b,big;
    printf("Enter two numbers \n");
    scanf("%f%f", &a, &b);
    
    big = a;
    if(b>big) big = b;
    printf("Largest number is : %f", big);
    return 0;
}

Output 

Enter two numbers 
90
80
Largest number is : 90.000000
  
Example 1.3

Given the basic pay of a employee, Write a program to calculate the HRA according to the following conditions.

Algorithm:

1. Input basic pay, bp
2. IF (bp < = 2000) THEN HRA = 200
3. IF (bp > 2000 and bp < = 4000) THEN HRA = 350
IF (bp > 4000) THEN HRA = 500
Output HRA 
STOP 

I Have Used this Method With My POV But Next Method is of Book both Answers r same but method not.

1st Method 

#include<stdio.h>
int main(){
    int bp;
    printf("Enter the basic pay : ");
    scanf("%d", &bp);
    if(bp < 2000)
    printf("HRA 200 \n");
    if(bp > 2000 && bp <= 4000)
    printf("HRA 350 \n");
    if(bp>4000)
    printf("HRA 500 \n");
    return 0;
}

Output 

Enter the basic pay : 2400
HRA 350 

2nd Method 

#include<stdio.h>
int main(){
    int bp, hra;
    printf("Enter the basic pay : ");
    scanf("%d", &bp);
    if(bp <= 2000) hra = 200;
    if(bp > 2000 && bp <= 4000) hra = 350;
    if(bp > 4000) hra = 500;
    printf("Hra is : %d", hra);
    return 0;
}

Output 

Enter the basic pay : 2400
Hra is : 350

IF... ELSE STATEMENT -----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

The General form of this statement is 

if(condition)
{ 
  statement-1;
}
else
{
  statement-2;
}

if the given condition is true then statement-1 is executed otherwise statement-2 will be executed. 

Some examples of the if.... else statement are given below.

1. if(a>b)
      big = a;
   else 
      big = b;
   
2. if(marks >= 40)
      printf("passed");
   else 
      printf("failed");
      
3.  if(number > 0)
   { 
     Sqroot = sqrt (number);
     printf("square root = %d", sqroot);
    }
    else 
        printf("Number is -ve");
        
        
Example 1.0

Write a program to find whether a given number is odd or even.

Algorithm :

1. Input a number, N
2. IF (N MOD 2) = 0 then
                    output 'Number is even'
   otherwise                 
                    output 'Number is odd'

3. STOP 
  
Program 

#include<stdio.h>
int main(){
    int N;
    printf("Enter the Number N :");
    scanf("%d", &N);
    
    if(N % 2 == 0)
    printf("Number is even");
    else
    printf("Number is odd");
    return 0;
}
    
Output 

Enter the Number N :9
Number is odd

Example 1.1

Develop a C program to find the largest of the three given numbers.

Steps:
1. Input three numbers a,b,c
2. (find the larger of two numbers and store the result in new variable, big.)
  IF(a>b) THEN big a ELSE big = b
3. (Compare the big and Third number, c, to get the result)
. IF (c>big) THEN big = c.
4.Output big 
5.STOP

#include<stdio.h>
int main(){
    int a,b,c, big;
    printf("Write the Number for a b & c \n");
    scanf("%d %d %d", &a, &b, &c);
    
    if(a > b) big = a; else big = b;
    
    if(c > big) big = c;
    printf("The Largest Number is :%d", big);
    return 0;
}

Output 

Write the Number for a b & c 
12
13
14
The Largest Number is :13

NESTED IF STATEMENTS ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

The if statement may contain one or more if statements. In such a case, they are said to be nested. An example of a nested if statement is shown below.

if condition-1
{
  if condition-2 
  {
       statement - 1;
  }
  else 
  {
       statement - 2;
  }
  
}
else
{
       statement 3;
}

If the condition-1 is true then the condition-2 is checked. If Condition-2 is true then statement-1 is executed, 
otherwise statement-2 is executed. if condition-1 is false, statement 3 is executed.

Example 1.0

#include<stdio.h>
int main(){
    float a,b,c,big;
    printf("Enter three numbers \n");
    scanf("%f%f%f", &a,&b,&c);
    
    if (a>b)
    {
        if(a>c) big = a; else big = c;
    }
    else 
    {
        if(b>c) big = b; else big = c;
    }
    printf("Largest number is : %6.2f \n", big);
    return 0;
}

Output 

Enter three numbers 
76
54
67
Largest number is :  76.00 

Write a Program using nested if statement ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Program 

#include<stdio.h>
int main(){
    int bp, hra;
    printf("Enter the basic payment :");
    scanf("%d", &bp);
    
    if(bp <=2000) hra = 200;
    else {
        if(bp <=4000) hra = 350;
        else
           hra = 500;
    }
    printf("HRA is : %d", hra);
    return 0;
}

Output 

Enter the basic payment :1300
HRA is : 200

  
